// syntax_error_tests.sigma
// This file contains deliberately malformed/edge-case scripts to exercise
// the recursive-descent parser's error reporting.

// 1) Misspelled directive keyword (should suggest `runcode`)
runcod println("typo in directive");

// 2) Misspelled function name (suggestion for println)
prontln("misspelled function name");

// 3) Incomplete arithmetic (missing RHS after '+')
println(2 + );

// 4) Extra/unexpected token (@ is not a valid operator)
println(1 @ 2);

// 5) Missing semicolon at end of statement
println("no semicolon")

// 6) Extra adjacent literals (unexpected token between literals)
println(1 2);

// 7) Associativity tests
// 7a: Force a right-child for a left-associative operator (+)
println(1 + (2 + 3));

// 7b: Force a left-child for the power operator (^) which must be right-associative
println((1 ^ 2) ^ 3);

// 8) Complex case: unterminated string
println("unterminated string);

// 9) Valid baseline (should not produce errors)
println("this line is valid");

// 10) Unterminated block comment
/* This block comment starts but does not end

// 11) Invalid numeric formats
println(.);           // lone dot
println(1.2.3);       // multiple dots
println(01x);         // invalid numeric literal

// 12) Missing comma in argument list
println("a" "b");

// 13) Trailing comma in args
println("a",);

// valid associativity example
println(1 + 2 + 3);

